<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-567-515  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 567 515.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 24 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for Unix: SCO's HCR/C+++ Release 3.0. (Santa Cruz Operation'sHCR/C++ 3.0 object-oriented programming language) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Woods, Wendy.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Santa Cruz Operation Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   HCR/C++ 3.0 (Compiler) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersProduct IntroductionProgram Development ToolsObject-Oriented Languages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR UNIX: SCO's HCR/C+++ Release 3.0 SANTA CRUZ, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1990OCT 24 (NB) -- Santa Cruz Operation says its HCR/C++ Release 3.0object-oriented programming language is now available for the SCO Unix SystemV/386 Release 3.2 operating system and Open Desktop, SCO's graphicaloperating system.andM;HCR/C++ Release 3.0 is an implementation of the ATandamp;T C++ Language SystemRelease 2.1 that has been enhanced to include the OSF/Motif-compatible dbXtradebugger, HCR/C++ Class Library Extensions, and complete documentation thatincludes library specifications and other reference material.andP;  HCR/C++ wasdeveloped by SCO Canada (formerly HCR, Inc.).andP;  SCO acquired HCR in May 1990.andM;Developers building Open Desktop-compatible applications can run the dbXtradebugger under Open Desktop's OSF/Motif interface.andP;  Used in conjunction withthe OSF/Motif user interface, HCR/C++ supports debugging with mouse input,button and menu definition, and multiple windows in which to examine sourcecode, variable values, and program output.andP;  Users may customize the OSF/Motifinterface by specifying the label and action associated with each button.andM;HCR/C++ is upwardly compatible with ANSI C. The SCO UNIX System V/386Development System or Open Desktop Development System is required to useHCR/C++.andM;SCO HRC/C++ is now available in dual-media packaging from all sales channelsin the U.S.andP;  and Canada for a list price of $1195, and also available fromdistributors in the Pacific, Asia, and Latin America.andM;(Wendy Woods/19901024)</TEXT></DOC>